Class OIOSamlObject

java.lang.Object
  dk.itst.oiosaml.sp.model.OIOSamlObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
OIOAbstractResponse, OIOAssertion, OIORequest
public class OIOSamlObject
extends Object

Base class for all SAML objects. This class defines default behavior, such as signature handling and serialization.

Author:
Joakim Recht

sign

public void sign(org.opensaml.xml.security.credential.Credential signingCredential)
Sign the saml object. The effect of calling this method is that a new Signature element is created, and the object is marshalled. If toXML() is called, the XML will contain a valid signature.

Parameters:
signingCredential - The credential used for signing the object.

Check that a given object has been signed correctly with a specific PublicKey.

Returns:
